summary: This document consists of two email exchanges on January 6, 2021, between individuals at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York, discussing scheduling a follow-up call related to an unspecified matter, likely connected to ongoing work of the Public Corruption Unit.

events.title: Email exchange regarding follow-up call
events.description: A Deputy Chief of the Public Corruption Unit emails 'M' to request a brief follow-up call, noting the team thinks it would be helpful for 'M' to reach out. A later email from another party mentions the day has been 'fairly crazed' and asks to speak the next morning.

keyFacts: The document is an email exchange dated January 6, 2021, involving personnel from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
The correspondence involves a Deputy Chief of the Public Corruption Unit, indicating activity within that unit.
The content suggests coordination for a follow-up call, with one participant describing the day as 'fairly crazed'.
